[thinking] **Exploring ClassLoader behavior**
[thinking] 
[thinking] I'm considering whether a rejecting ClassLoader that rejects all classes could cause `Class.forName("java.util.ArrayList", false, rejectingClassLoader)` in Native Image to throw `UnsupportedFeatureError` instead of `ClassNotFoundException`. It seems like native images may not support custom classloaders, and at runtime, the classloader is largely irrelevant. If the class is registered, `Class.forName` might return with any loader. But if it throws `UnsupportedFeatureError`, then the test may fail. I should definitely double-check GraalVM Native Image specifics on this!
