Lb_83ojQrul0lM2sjSBzUdM6xWoUEi_38bGxaPrm46uovfQ8guB12gD3K0Llrwk045USCN6LXAXolImf7Wopt03AAYgEHx5j_xlkGgmzzkBRJNN9WRJhqwgv-R8yc7cjacw3eAr7XD2L4pL9jVtyj3_jp_zvfXnx_k-ZohGuTARZXnqgtFmEYhtv881SaL-r2ejJHiUP27J7TZdHO4So3CzBZ1JIKUnEqgfs0QED2iDrBLGVpRZby6rspvyZ1_wM6JplDa9KgXBYi6QOt-dDP9xJQk9nhQ_6SuVpeMRtmLU7hOTeNn0CfJ2m7ziUUSp8UeR5b5gkD3HM7LP47PoMnFxctWGNE25fL4t4A61QGm4u1ZRFiRUKxf1KvO9knqAFyxdEcRk7CmdNoMipTzpkdg\",\"summary\":[{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Exploring ClassLoader behavior**\\n\\nI'm considering whether a rejecting ClassLoader that rejects all classes could cause `Class.forName(\\\"java.util.ArrayList\\\", false, rejectingClassLoader)` in Native Image to throw `UnsupportedFeatureError` instead of `ClassNotFoundException`. It seems like native images may not support custom classloaders, and at runtime, the classloader is largely irrelevant. If the class is registered, `Class.forName` might return with any loader. But if it throws `UnsupportedFeatureError`, then the test may fail. I should definitely double-check GraalVM Native Image specifics on this!\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Analyzing class loading failures**\\n\\nI’m thinking about how, if a class fails to load, I might need to catch `UnsupportedFeatureError` around the fallback test. However, if the call site doesn't reach super in native, tests might not execute under the expected conditions. If custom classloaders are fundamentally unsupported, there's a verification catch that could skip coverage in native. It might be better to avoid using custom ClassLoaders by constructing one that throws `ClassNotFoundException` in both JVM and Native Image.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_yirb12JhNhQJojsLhc2b27Ru|fc_0ebade7d17e6e4a00169fb290a52f481a1b17dbf8f1d4df7bb", "name": "write", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/com.typesafe.akka/akka-actor_2.13/2.8.8/src/test/scala/com_typesafe_akka/akka_actor_2_13/ClassLoaderObjectInputStreamTest.scala", "content": "/*\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\n *\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\n */\npackage com_typesafe_akka.akka_actor_2_13\n\nimport java.io.ByteArrayInputStream\nimport java.io.ByteArrayOutputStream\nimport java.io.ObjectOutputStream\nimport java.io.Serializable\n\nimport akka.util.ClassLoaderObjectInputStream\nimport org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test\n\nclass ClassLoaderObjectInputStreamTest {\n  @Test\n  def deserializesUsingProvidedClassLoader(): Unit = {\n    val expected: ClassLoaderObjectInputStreamPayload = serializablePayload()\n    val bytes: Array[Byte] = serialize(expected)\n\n    val actual: ClassLoaderObjectInputStreamPayload = deserialize(bytes, getClass.getClassLoader)\n      .asInstanceOf[ClassLoaderObjectInputStreamPayload]\n\n    assertThat(actual.message).isEqualTo(expected.message)\n  }\n\n  @Test\n  def fallsBackToObjectInputStreamClassResolutionWhenProvidedClassLoaderCannotLoadClass(): Unit = {\n    val expected: ClassLoaderObjectInputStreamPayload = serializablePayload()\n    val bytes: Array[Byte] = serialize(expected)\n\n    val actual: ClassLoaderObjectInputStreamPayload = deserialize(bytes, null)\n      .asInstanceOf[ClassLoaderObjectInputStreamPayload]\n\n    assertThat(actual.message).isEqualTo(expected.message)\n  }\n\n  private def serializablePayload(): ClassLoaderObjectInputStreamPayload = {\n    new ClassLoaderObjectInputStreamPayload(\"akka serialization\")\n  }\n\n  private def serialize(value: AnyRef): Array[Byte] = {\n    val bytes: ByteArrayOutputStream = new ByteArrayOutputStream()\n    val output: ObjectOutputStream = new ObjectOutputStream(bytes)\n    try {\n      output.writeObject(value)\n    } finally {\n      output.close()\n    }\n    bytes.toByteArray\n  }\n\n  private def deserialize(bytes: Array[Byte], classLoader: ClassLoader): AnyRef = {\n    val input: ClassLoaderObjectInputStream = new ClassLoaderObjectInputStream(\n      classLoader,\n      new ByteArrayInputStream(bytes))\n    try {\n      input.readObject().asInstanceOf[AnyRef]\n    } finally {\n      input.close()\n    }\n  }\n}\n\nfinal class ClassLoaderObjectInputStreamPayload(val message: String) extends Serializable\n"}, "partialJson": "{\"path\":\"tests/src/com.typesafe.akka/akka-actor_2.13/2.8.8/src/test/scala/com_typesafe_akka/akka_actor_2_13/ClassLoaderObjectInputStreamTest.scala\",\"content\":\"/*\\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\\n *\\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\\n */\\npackage com_typesafe_akka.akka_actor_2_13\\n\\nimport java.io.ByteArrayInputStream\\nimport java.io.ByteArrayOutputStream\\nimport java.io.ObjectOutputStream\\nimport java.io.Serializable\\n\\nimport akka.util.ClassLoaderObjectInputStream\\nimport org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat\\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test\\n\\nclass ClassLoaderObjectInputStreamTest {\\n  @Test\\n  def deserializesUsingProvidedClassLoader(): Unit = {\\n    val expected: ClassLoaderObjectInputStreamPayload = serializablePayload()\\n    val bytes: Array[Byte] = serialize(expected)\\n\\n    val actual: ClassLoaderObjectInputStreamPayload = deserialize(bytes, getClass.getClassLoader)\\n      .asInstanceOf[ClassLoaderObjectInputStreamPayload]\\n\\n    assertThat(actual.message).isEqualTo(expected.message)\\n  }\\n\\n  @Test\\n  def fallsBackToObjectInputStreamClassResolutionWhenProvidedClassLoaderCannotLoadClass(): Unit = {\\n    val expected: ClassLoaderObjectInputStreamPayload = serializablePayload()\\n    val bytes: Array[Byte] = serialize(expected)\\n\\n    val actual: ClassLoaderObjectInputStreamPayload = deserialize(bytes, null)\\n      .asInstanceOf[ClassLoaderObjectInputStreamPayload]\\n\\n    assertThat(actual.message).isEqualTo(expected.message)\\n  }\\n\\n  private def seri